description.narrative: Develop and roll out capacity development tools for UNICEF staff, particularly Early Child Development (ECD) focal points in COs and in humanitarian crises (e.g. self learning programme in AGORA) to strengthen inter-sectoral Early Child Development (ECD) programme delivery and policies, which contributes to Early Childhood Development, Early Childhood Development (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Every Child to Survive and Thrive By 2021, countries apply child-sensitive policies, innovative community-centered approaches and evidence, to implement development and humanitarian interventions at scale, that enable Every Child to Survive and Thrive

title.narrative: Develop and roll out capacity development tools for UNICEF staff, particularly ECD focal points in COs and in humanitarian crises(e.g. self learning programme in AGORA) to strengthen inter-sectoral ECD programme delivery and policies

description.narrative: Despite the continuous restrictions due to the COVID-19 pandemic, the ECD team strengthened its technical support in more than 40 countries to enhance the enabling environment and the uptake of multi-sectoral ECD programming and parenting support. ECD programme excellence was elevated through: (i) the development of a global programme strategy/assets, including the organizational Parenting Strategy and Care for Caregivers (CFC) training package; (ii) operationalization of the Nurturing Care Framework (NCF); (iii) policy advocacy and systems strengthening, including for family-friendly policies (FFP) and public financing for ECD; and (iv) capacity development of UNICEF staff and partners. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:25/03/2022
